elite who use the levers of political power to channel foreign capital into real estate and manufacturing projects, conspicuous consumption is a means of projecting an image of Asian ascendancy to potential investors. For Viet Kieus and Westerners who bring remittances into the local economy, personal relationships with local sex workers reinforce their ideas of Asia’s rise and Western decline, while simultaneously bolstering their diminished masculinity. Dealing in Desire illuminates Ho Chi Minh City’s sex industry as not just a microcosm of the global economy, but a critical space where dreams and deals are traded.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSex industryzVietnam. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aasian businessmen.  abiography.  ablack market.  abudget tourist.  acounselor.  adecline of western civilization.  aethnography.  aillegal trade.  ainformal economy.  amodern slavery.  apsychologist.  arise of asia.  asaigon hostess bars.  asex trade.  asex trafficking.  asex worker.  asex workers.  asexual slavery.  asuper-elite.  asurvivor.  atherapist.  aviet kieus.  avietnam.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052027555340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096068840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520960688423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520960688/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY